He seems to be· long to the class ol dogs commonly found on vases ol this period which were chiefly used lor hunting⁴⁵ and whose cousins the Lacedaemoniam hounds enjoyed a high reputation among the ancients. The warrior resembles strongly the youth on the Psiax alabastron in Odessa⁴⁶. The warrior here however is adjusting his helmet on his head and not raising it as on the alabastron47.
